         <abstract>
            <p>The paper is concerned with the Chebyshev approximation of decay-type functions f(x) by interpolating rationals. The interpolating points are chosen to be the zeros of f(x). Existence, uniqueness and characterization of best approximations are first shown. An exchange algorithm is then described for computing the best approximation.</p>
